txt.en: The Uruk-general Zaukîl can be found atop a hill at the heart of the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.

The Uruk-general Zaukîl can be found atop a hill at the heart of the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\n\nYou should slay Zaukîl, the Uruk-general of Dol Dínen, and bring back his armour as proof of the deed.

The Uruk-general Zaukîl can be found atop a hill at the heart of the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\n\nYou should slay Zaukîl, the Uruk-general of Dol Dínen, and bring back his armour as proof of the deed.
'This is a fine trophy. Though the second Uruk-general will likely not view you as a worthy challenge, this may play to his vanity.'
Defeat Zaukîl and collect his armour
Arohir awaits you at Esteldín.\n\nOne of the two Uruk-generals leading the Orc horde has been slain at your hand. Arohir will want to hear of your victory.
'The defeat of the Uruk-general at Dol Dínen has earned you great favour among the Dúnedain of the North, [placeholder].'
'Did you bring me any evidence of your deeds? How am I to believe you? Come back to me when you have a piece of his armour as proof.'
'Your courage has lent us time to prepare. Well done, [placeholder]!'
'Your courage has lent us time to prepare. Well done, [placeholder]!'
'This is a fine trophy, [placeholder]! I am pleased that this Zaukîl roams the earth no longer.'
